               <head>Grant; Needham Street; 1317</head>
               <msContents><textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111667">Needham Street (Needham-Street)</placeName>. 
                        <origDate when="1317">1317</origDate>. 
                        Grant from <persName nymRef="ad caput ville">
                           <forename>Juliana</forename>, widow of <persName>
                              <forename>Radulf</forename> '<surname>ad caput ville</surname>' of <placeName role="person" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName>
                           </persName></persName>, to <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Priour</surname>
                        </persName> of the same, of 2.5 acres of arable land of which 2 acres lie in the crofts of Nedham in the west side, one at the upper end, lying between the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> 
                           <surname>Pyle</surname></persName>, and the fee of the <persName>Lady <forename>Cescilia</forename> Le <surname>Talemache</surname></persName>, and abutting on a messuage once held by the said Radulf; which the half acre lies in Peinelnecroftis, on the east, between the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Beylard</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111664">Kentford (Kenteford)</placeName></persName>, bought from <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> le <surname>Marcer</surname></persName>, and abutting on the messuage of <persName>John le <surname>Warner</surname></persName>.
                        Dated, at <placeName role="date" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName>, Friday, the feast of St Botulf, abbot, 10 Ed. II [17 June, 1317]
                     Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> le <surname>Mercer</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Gilbert</forename> of <surname>Honedene</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Sperling</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> le <surname>Warner</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> 
                           <surname>Persoun</surname></persName>, <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Fabr</surname></persName>', <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> de <surname>Appetone</surname></persName>, and others.
                     </p>
